<section class="problem reveal" id="problem">
  <div class="inner">
    <div class="sec-label">Sound Familiar?</div>
    <h2>When things get busy,<br>the back end quietly breaks down.</h2>
    <div class="problem-grid">
      <div class="p-card reveal"><div class="p-bar"></div><div class="p-title">Bookings Slip Through</div><p class="p-text">Follow-ups don't go out. Clients quietly book somewhere else without you ever knowing.</p></div>
      <div class="p-card reveal d1"><div class="p-bar"></div><div class="p-title">Invoices Pile Up</div><p class="p-text">Estimates sit unsent. Cash flow tightens for no reason other than not enough hours in the day.</p></div>
      <div class="p-card reveal d2"><div class="p-bar"></div><div class="p-title">Inquiries Go Unanswered</div><p class="p-text">New patients reach out and don't hear back. They move on and you never knew the opportunity was there.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="problem-note reveal">
      <p><strong>None of this is your fault.</strong> It's what happens when there aren't enough hours in the day. That's exactly what we fix.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
